{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">noncomputable def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./LCS/Games/MagicSquare.html#Strat_merminPeres\"><span class=\"name\">Strat_merminPeres</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./LCS/Strategy/ObservableStrategy.html#ObservableStrategyData\">ObservableStrategyData</a> <a href=\"./LCS/Games/MagicSquare.html#mat16\">mat16</a> <a href=\"./LCS/Games/MagicSquare.html#magic_square_layout\">magic_square_layout</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The Mermin-Peres strategy for the magic square game.\nThis strategy uses `BipartiteObservableStrategy` to lift the 9 `MP_observables` to a\nvalid `ObservableStrategyData` on a 16x16 bipartite space. It relies on\n`MP_sameEquation_comm` to satisfy the commutativity constraints for each equation. ","docLink":"./LCS/Games/MagicSquare.html#Strat_merminPeres","kind":"def","line":175,"name":"Strat_merminPeres","sourceLink":"https://github.com/sean-prz/lean/blob/caca813376ed07fc5f820b376b03a4766a45af86/projects/LCS/LCS/Games/MagicSquare.lean#L175-L180"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./LCS/Games/MagicSquare.html#MP_sameEquation_comm\"><span class=\"name\">MP_sameEquation_comm</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">6</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Logic/Pairwise.html#Pairwise\">Pairwise</a> <span class=\"fn\">fun (<span class=\"fn\">j</span> <span class=\"fn\">k</span> : <span class=\"fn\">↥<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./LCS/Games/MagicSquare.html#magic_square_layout\">magic_square_layout</a>.<a href=\"./LCS/Basic.html#LCSLayout.V\">V</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span>)</span></span>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Commute/Defs.html#Commute\">Commute</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./LCS/Games/MagicSquare.html#magic_square_grid\">magic_square_grid</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">j</span></span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./LCS/Games/MagicSquare.html#magic_square_grid\">magic_square_grid</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">k</span></span>)</span></span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For every equation of the layout, the associated grid observables commute pairwise. ","docLink":"./LCS/Games/MagicSquare.html#MP_sameEquation_comm","kind":"theorem","line":153,"name":"MP_sameEquation_comm","sourceLink":"https://github.com/sean-prz/lean/blob/caca813376ed07fc5f820b376b03a4766a45af86/projects/LCS/LCS/Games/MagicSquare.lean#L153-L164"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./LCS/Games/MagicSquare.html#tacticSolve_line_comm\"><span class=\"name\">tacticSolve_line_comm</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">Lean.ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A tactic for proving pairwise commutativity within one row or column of the square. ","docLink":"./LCS/Games/MagicSquare.html#tacticSolve_line_comm","kind":"def","line":92,"name":"tacticSolve_line_comm","sourceLink":"https://github.com/sean-prz/lean/blob/caca813376ed07fc5f820b376b03a4766a45af86/projects/LCS/LCS/Games/MagicSquare.lean#L92-L114"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./LCS/Games/MagicSquare.html#magic_square_is_observable\"><span class=\"name\">magic_square_is_observable</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">j</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">9</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./LCS/Observable.html#IsObservable\">IsObservable</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./LCS/Games/MagicSquare.html#magic_square_grid\">magic_square_grid</a> <span class=\"fn\">j</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Each observable in the Mermin-Peres grid is a self-adjoint involution. ","docLink":"./LCS/Games/MagicSquare.html#magic_square_is_observable","kind":"theorem","line":69,"name":"magic_square_is_observable","sourceLink":"https://github.com/sean-prz/lean/blob/caca813376ed07fc5f820b376b03a4766a45af86/projects/LCS/LCS/Games/MagicSquare.lean#L69-L79"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./LCS/Games/MagicSquare.html#magic_square_grid\"><span class=\"name\">magic_square_grid</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">9</span></span> → <a href=\"./LCS/Games/MagicSquare.html#mat4\">mat4</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The 9 observables for the Mermin-Peres magic square, defined as Kronecker products of\nPauli matrices (X, Y, Z) and the identity (I2). ","docLink":"./LCS/Games/MagicSquare.html#magic_square_grid","kind":"def","line":56,"name":"magic_square_grid","sourceLink":"https://github.com/sean-prz/lean/blob/caca813376ed07fc5f820b376b03a4766a45af86/projects/LCS/LCS/Games/MagicSquare.lean#L56-L67"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./LCS/Games/MagicSquare.html#magic_square_layout\"><span class=\"name\">magic_square_layout</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./LCS/Basic.html#LCSLayout\">LCSLayout</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The layout of the Mermin-Peres magic square game.\nIt consists of 6 equations (3 rows and 3 columns) over 9 variables (the cells of the 3x3 grid). ","docLink":"./LCS/Games/MagicSquare.html#magic_square_layout","kind":"def","line":30,"name":"magic_square_layout","sourceLink":"https://github.com/sean-prz/lean/blob/caca813376ed07fc5f820b376b03a4766a45af86/projects/LCS/LCS/Games/MagicSquare.lean#L30-L43"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./LCS/Games/MagicSquare.html#mat16\"><span class=\"name\">mat16</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The 16×16 matrix type used for the bipartite lift of the two-qubit strategy. ","docLink":"./LCS/Games/MagicSquare.html#mat16","kind":"def","line":21,"name":"mat16","sourceLink":"https://github.com/sean-prz/lean/blob/caca813376ed07fc5f820b376b03a4766a45af86/projects/LCS/LCS/Games/MagicSquare.lean#L21-L22"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./LCS/Games/MagicSquare.html#mat4\"><span class=\"name\">mat4</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The 4×4 matrix type used for two-qubit observables in the magic square construction. ","docLink":"./LCS/Games/MagicSquare.html#mat4","kind":"def","line":19,"name":"mat4","sourceLink":"https://github.com/sean-prz/lean/blob/caca813376ed07fc5f820b376b03a4766a45af86/projects/LCS/LCS/Games/MagicSquare.lean#L19-L20"}}],"imports":["Init","LCS.Basic","LCS.Observable","LCS.Strategy.ObservableStrategy","LCS.Pauli"],"instances":[],"name":"LCS.Games.MagicSquare"}